>>0e59a696-698e-449a-a0c4-47b06f007388
Nadler's episode could have been a number of things, but if neurological symptoms suddenly resolve it is usually referred to as  TIA (transient ischemic attack) which is a warning of possible future stroke which can cause permanent damage without some intervention within a window of about 4 hours.  If it was a TIA, he would have been hospitalized for a neuro workup and I don't recall hearing that he was, so probably something else. A lot of things can cause neuro symptoms, drugs, lack of sleep, panic attacks, sudden drop in blood pressure, etc.
